About
De Hallen, a cultural hub with a social heart located in Amsterdam-West since 2014 in a former tramdepot. National monument. A vibrant center for fashion, art, culture, hospitality and crafts. Eat & Drink In the FoodHallen you will find a collection of the most tasteful and varied cuisines. Right behind is the Kanarie Club, a spacious restaurant with a lovely terrace, and Remise47, the restaurant of Hotel de Hallen. Enjoy a delicious cup of coffee and a good book in the Belcampo reading café, the living room of the neighborhood. Art & Culture De Filmhallen with its 9 screens is a must-see for every film lover. Opposite you’ll find Beeldend Gesproken, a gallery for contemporary art. Right across is thr public library (OBA). Recycle is a bike shop/workshop training people in bike repair. At the Maker Market you will find cool local brands. Denim City connects denim experts and includes Jean School, partnering with top brands. Kinki Academy trains future hairdressers.
Duration: 2-3 hours
